text:
LV17 TMO (Thu/Fri/Sat nights, 24 hour run Mon 9am to Tue 9am)

Single shot attosecond imaging. Exploring if there are nonlinear effects which could be helpful for coherent diffractive imaging for FELs. One application is improving the brightness/spatial resolution of images that are typically resolution-limited due to sample damage

  • Will scan over photon energies (830-1000 eV range using 4.5 GeV electrons), both coarsely and finely
    • Coarse will likely use undulators, fine will likely use vernier scan as long as pulse intensity doesn't suffer too much
  • Maximum pulse energy (highest photon power density possible), especially for shortest pulses
  • Will change pulse duration: want 0.5, 1, 5, 10-20 fs pulses, and 50-100fs as a reference
    • Experimenter expressed that it may be okay to do 10 fs or so for the 'shortish' pulses so we can use tricks like half charge etc.
  • Gas attenuator will be used, especially for higher pulse durations (want to compare 50fs to 5fs for instance)
    • Gas detector calibration very important as they need to know power precisely

Shift breakdown (rough, subject to change)

  • Thu:
    • SASE, 840-880 eV scan
    • Full beam, 50-70 fs
  • Fri:
    • XLEAP, 830-980 eV scan

    • Max pulse energy
  • Sat:
    • Fewish femtoseconds (likely half charge, possible slotted foil, experimenter can likely deal with 10fs)
    • 830-980 ev scan
    • Max pulse energy
  • Mon 24 hour run
    • Few fs to 30 fs (likely half charge, possible slotted foil, experimenter can likely deal with 10fs)
    • 830-980 eV scan
    • Full beam, 50-70 fs
